HEADWORD: Extensible
<hw>Ex*ten"si*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>extensible</ets>. See <er>Extend</er>.]</ety> <def>Capable of being
extended, whether in length or breadth; susceptible of enlargement;
extensible; extendible; -- the opposite of <contr>contractible</contr>
or <contr>compressible</contr>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧An <xex>extensible</xex>
membrane⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Holder.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Extensibleness</ent>⟦br⟧
